Nigerian author Chimamanda Ngozi Adichie is the cover star of Marie Claire Brazil’s magazine and we couldn’t be more proud. She shared the cover image on  Instagram on Saturday. “Delighted to be on the cover of Marie Claire Brazil. And to highlight the work of talented designers: Brazilian @renatabuzzo.veglab and Nigerians @kikikamanu and @the_ladymaker,” she said in the post. She expressed her gratitude to a few people at the magazine who made the cover happened and for “everyone at the Marie Claire Brazil team for taking a stand for feminism.” Take a look at the alluring cover photos below. <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-896292 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-922x1152.jpg" alt="" width="922" height="1152" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-922x1152.jpg 922w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-478x598.jpg 478w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-446x557.jpg 446w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-891x1114.jpg 891w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-192x240.jpg 192w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-384x480.jpg 384w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-480x600.jpg 480w,https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire.jpg 1048w" sizes="(max-width: 922px) 100vw, 922px" /> <img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-896289 lazyload" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-Brazil5-922x1152.jpg" alt="" width="922" height="1152" srcset="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2019/04/Chimamanda-Ngozi-Adichie-marie-Claire-Brazil5-922x1152.jpg 922w,https://guardi